'''Klæburuten''' is a   located in . It operates the regional buses in  and to  in addition to the Airport Bus from Trondheim to .
The bus company operates 26 daily buses between Trondheim and Klæbu. In Trondheim buses stop both at  and . The Airport Bus is operated at 15 minutes  between the airport and town, with stops at most major hotels in town.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.klaburuten.no/ |title=Historikk |author=Klæburuten |accessdate=2007-01-19}}</ref> In total the company has 10 city buses, 11 charter coaches and 21 airport coaches.
The company started out in  when Arnt Krokum started '''Krokum Bilruter'''. The company started with one bus, then added a second in . In  the company started a bus service for  between Trondheim and  and . In  the company was converted to a  and four years later the company started a bus service to Trondheim Airport, Værnes on contract with . The company started with  trips in the 1950s, and still has the same three main activities and still has only one dominant owner.<ref>{{cite book |last=|coauthors= |title=Rutehefte for Trondheim og Klæbu |year=2006}}</ref>
